  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Using the Sustainable Livelihoods Approach to identify Family Support needs</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project builds on two previous projects carried out by ATDFW using the Sustainable Livelihoods Approach to inform their work with people in poverty (see ENGA62). This new grant will fund intensive work with families living on a low income, to identify their hopes and assets, and to agree a way forward. This will be carefully monitored to identify positive changes as well as challenges, to help ATDFW in future project design and fund raising. Project findings will also inform on -going advocacy work on welfare reform and services for people living in poverty in England.</narrative>
  </description>
